cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object recognition and feature matching in cluttered scenes using depth images. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed method can be applied to robotic perception tasks. Additionally, the use of histograms and eigenvectors suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of mesh data and point data suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
